/* This example demonstrates how the FaCT compiler does not allow accesses of
 * memory by a secret value, since such accesses can reveal the secret value. A
 * potential workaround, at the cost of performance, would be to iterate through
 * all elements of buf and to only write 0 to the element of interest. */
void set_to_zero(
    secret mut uint32[] buf,
    secret uint64 i) {
  buf[i] = 0;
}
